news.title: China: Shimao Group seeks ABS extensions; shares, bonds sell off
news.para: Shimao Group's unit Shanghai Shimao Construction has proposed extensions on maturities for two asset-backed securities (ABS) due this month totalling 1.17 billion yuan ($183.50 million), three sources with knowledge of the matter told Reuters.

news.title: Drop in income during covid hits Lucknow civic body property tax collection target
news.para: According to LMC officials, against the target of Rs 34 crore property tax collection set for the three-month period from September to November, the municipal corporation has only managed to collect around Rs 5 crore so far.

news.title: Ashok Piramal Group's Peninsula Land defaults on Rs 77.24-crore debt obligations
news.para: The company owes Rs 66.14 crore as principal to RBL Bank at a 12.5% interest rate, a principal amount of Rs 172 crore to the State Bank of India at 9.05% and Rs 18.63 crore to Axis Bank at a 9.75% interest rate as on December 30. All of these are secured loans, the company said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: NRAI writes to top mall owners, landlords seeking rental waiver for F&B retailers
news.para: The NRAI also sought minimum guaranteed rents for three months after that and instead work on a pure revenue share model.

news.title: Land acquisition for Kochi Metro to be completed next month
news.para: The government issued a primary notification for the acquisition of an additional land in Kanayannur taluk on December 28, after the social impact assessment (SIA) study conducted by the Rajagiri Outreach showed green signal for the acquisition.

news.title: Macrotech Developers forms 11 JVs since April 2021 to develop projects worth Rs 14,500 crore
news.para: Mumbai-based Macrotech Developers, which is one of the leading real estate developers in India, markets its properties under Lodha brand. It got listed on stock exchanges after raising Rs 2,500 crore from Initial Public Offer (IPO).

news.title: Panaji market tenants to get eviction notices
news.para: Of the 446 tenants that were operating rent-free, only19 have come forward to sign the agreement after the Corporation of the City of Panaji (CCP) started the process from October 2021 onwards.

news.title: Kerala government to acquire 20 acres land to rehabilitate Parvathy Puthanar families
news.para: Kerala waterways and infrastructure limited (KWIL) chief engineer had requested for taking steps to acquire the land measuring 20.06 acres of land owned by private parties for rehabilitation purposes.

news.title: Tamil Nadu government looks to extend validity of planning permissions
news.para: The government has decided to amend the Tamil Nadu Town and Country Planning Act, 1971, to extend the validity of planning permissions from five years to eight years,A bill to this effect was tabled in the Assembly by housing and urban development minister S Muthusamy on Thursday.

news.title: Nyay Nagar plot buyers seek help from Indore collector
news.para: Collector Manish Singh and other senior administrative officials on Thursday took stock of A, B and C sector of Nyay Nagar and heard grievances of the plot buyers. During this, the collector ordered the officials concerned to remove encroachments from the plots.

news.title: Ludhiana: Draw of lots for Atal Apartments on January 10
news.para: The applicants can check their names on a list that the LIT has put on its website. The LIT claims that the HIG flats had received a better response than the MIG flats and the draw will be conducted under the Covid protocol, which has been conveyed to the applicants.

news.title: Macrotech Developers' sales bookings up 40% to Rs 2,608 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: In a regulatory filing, Macrotech said its sales bookings grew to Rs 2,608 crore during the third quarter of this fiscal, from Rs 1,862 crore in the year-ago period. The sales bookings number pertains to its projects in India. On Wednesday, the company had reported sales bookings of Rs 1,900 crore in its two projects in London.

news.title: Nashik: Commercial, residential buildings need to finish fire audit by Feb 10
news.para: In the case of the residential buildings, fire audits will be applicable for those structures having a height of more than 15 metres.

news.title: Hetero Group acquires 600 acres in Hyderabad for over Rs 350 crore from US fund
news.para: "Hetero has a joint development partnership with RMZ Corp and K Raheja Group to develop commercial properties in Hyderabad, totalling 20 acres of land," said one of the people quoted earlier.

news.title: Tamil Nadu red-flags BSNL's Rs 1,250 crore Chennai asset 'monetisation' plan
news.para: BSNL has identified eight prime properties for sale in the first phase. The revenue objection was raised when the BSNL officials approached the former for patta transfer-related issue.
